Aim: Consider any Airline Reservation System. Design a database containing tables/fields as route_id, origin, destination, fare, distance, capacity. 
Write a procedure to satisfy the following conditions accepting the route_id as the user  input.
•	If the distance is less than 500 then update the fare to be 190.98
•	If the distance is between 501-1000 then update fare to be 876
•	If the distance is greater than 1000 then display a message.

Solution:
Table Creation
CREATE TABLE route_header (
    route_id NUMBER(5),
    origin VARCHAR2(20),
    destination VARCHAR2(20),
    fare NUMBER(7,2),
    distance NUMBER(3),
    capacity NUMBER(3)
);

Data Insertion
INSERT INTO route_header VALUES (102, 'trichy', 'madurai', 33, 450, 56);
INSERT INTO route_header VALUES (103, 'madurai', 'madras', 35, 250, 50);
INSERT INTO route_header VALUES (104, 'madurai', 'madras', 35, 250, 50);
INSERT INTO route_header VALUES (105, 'madurai', 'madras', 35, 250, 50);

Procedure
CREATE OR REPLACE PROCEDURE router_header_proc1 (routeid route_header.route_id%type) AS
  a NUMBER(7,2);
  b NUMBER(4);
BEGIN
  SELECT fare, distance INTO a, b FROM route_header WHERE route_id = routeid;

  IF b < 500 THEN
    UPDATE route_header SET fare = 190.98 WHERE route_id = routeid;
  ELSIF b BETWEEN 501 AND 1000 THEN
    UPDATE route_header SET fare = 800.00 WHERE route_id = routeid;
  ELSIF b > 1000 THEN
    DBMS_OUTPUT.put_line('Sorry, distance is too large.');
  END IF;
END;
/
Explanation:
•	Table Creation: We create a route_header table that stores details about different airline routes, including route_id, origin, destination, fare, distance, and capacity.
•	Data Insertion: We insert sample data into the route_header table.
•	Procedure:
o	The procedure router_header_proc1 takes routeid as input and fetches the fare and distance for that route.
o	Based on the distance, it updates the fare:
	If the distance is less than 500, the fare is set to 190.98.
	If the distance is between 501 and 1000, the fare is updated to 800.00.
	If the distance is greater than 1000, it displays a message.


Outcome: This practical helps students understand how to update database records conditionally using PL/SQL procedures.


